main event: Two rectangular, white objects were observed hovering and maneuvering slowly on the ground in Norristown, Pennsylvania on September 8, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were observed for approximately 10 minutes.
The objects were described as being approximately 4 inches in length and 2 inches in width, with a slight glow.
The objects were observed to move slightly on the ground.
The weather was clear with no clouds.
The terrain where the objects were observed was a gravel/rocky surface.
photographs: yes, the report includes two photographs of the objects
